ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me now look at the design system components and check a few more 
critical things. I also need to check whether there are widget tests, and whethe
r the BDD step definitions are complete.\n\nKey observations so far:\n\n1. **Blo
cking**: `make test` and `make lint` were NOT executed. The PR body says "⚠️ 后端
测试因环境缺失 ts-jest 无法运行" and "⚠️ ESLint v9 与项目 .eslintrc.js 不兼容". A
ccording to the fullstack feature template checklist, `make test` and `make lint
` are mandatory.\n\n2. **Blocking**: `sequence_id` does NOT use database auto-in
crement `bigserial` as explicitly required by PRD v1-im.md. The code uses `Snowf
lake.nextId()` application-level ID generation. The migration creates `sequence_
id BIGINT NOT NULL` without `AUTO_INCREMENT`. The entity doesn\'t use any auto-g
eneration decorator. The docs/modules/im.md incorrectly says "使用数据库自增 big
serial" but the code doesn\'t actually do this.\n\n3. **Major**: `createSystemMe
ssage` has no duplicate protection. System messages have `client_message_id = nu
ll`, and MySQL unique indexes allow multiple NULL values. If `match:created` eve
nt is fired twice (e.g., retry or race condition), duplicate welcome messages wi
ll be created. The PRD says: "打开会话时，若数据库中无系统消息记录，后端自动插入
一条".\n\n4. **Major**: `matching.module.ts` was NOT updated to import `ImModule
` as claimed in the PR description. The diff shows it only replaced Redis direct
instantiation with `RedisModule` and added `JwtModule`. The PR body claims "更新
matching.module.ts - 引入 ImModule" but this is false. While `MatchingService` u
ses `EventEmitter2` instead of direct `ImService` dependency, the PR description
is misleading and could indicate missing integration. However, since EventEmitte
r2 is used, this isn\'t technically a bug in the code, just an inaccurate PR des
cription.\n\nWait, but does `ImModule` need to be imported in `AppModule` for th
e event emitter to work? Yes, and it is. `@nestjs/event-emitter` needs `EventEmi
tterModule.forRoot()` in the app module. Let me check if that\'s in app.module.t
s.\n\n5. **Minor**: In `im.service.ts` `getConversations`, the raw SQL uses `?` 
placeholders which is correct per template. Good.\n\n6. **Minor**: The `next_cur
sor` in `getMessages` uses `messages[0].sequence_id` after reverse. Since `messa
ges[0]` is the oldest in the page after reverse, the next page will load message
s with `sequence_id < oldest_sequence_id`. This is correct for loading older mes
sages. However, for the first page, the cursor is the oldest of the latest 20 me
ssages. If a new message arrives after the first load, the second page might hav
e overlap or gaps. But this is standard cursor pagination and acceptable for MVP
.\n\n7. **Minor**: `im.gateway.ts` emits `message:delivered` only if receiver is
online at the exact moment of sending. But the receiver might connect later. The
re\'s no mechanism to send `delivered` when the receiver comes online and reads 
pending messages. This is acceptable for MVP but noted.\n\n8. **Minor**: `chat_p
age.dart` has good accessibility with Semantics. But it uses `onTapDown` for but
tons instead of `onTap`. The AGENTS.md mentions Flutter UI spec. I should check 
the Flutter spec to see if this is required.\n\nWait, I haven\'t read the Flutte
r spec yet. Let me check it quickly.\n\nActually, I should also check if there a
re any issues with the `docs/modules/im.md` paths. It says:\n- `packages/design-
system/lib/src/molecules/chat_bubble.dart` but the actual files are `sw_chat_bub
ble.dart`. So the module doc has incorrect paths.\n\n9. **Minor**: `Conversation
ListPage` calls `context.read<ConversationListCubit>().fetchConversations()` on 
initState but doesn\'t check if the widget is still mounted after async operatio
ns. However, `BlocBuilder` handles state changes safely.\n\n10. **Minor**: The `
ConversationListPage` listens to `ImBloc` for `ConversationListNeedsRefresh` and
`MessagesLoaded` with `lastReadMessageId` changes. But `ImBloc` and `Conversatio
nListCubit` are separate - there might be state synchronization issues.\n\nLet m
e check the Flutter UI spec quickly to see if `onTapDown` is the required patter
n.',
    encrypted=None
)
