ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me review a few more critical points:\n\n1. The `matching.module.
ts` change: It does NOT import `ImModule`. The PR description is inaccurate. How
ever, the event emitter pattern works because `EventEmitterModule.forRoot()` is 
in `AppModule` and `ImModule` is also in `AppModule`. So `MatchingService` can e
mit events and `ImService` can listen. This is actually fine, but the PR descrip
tion is misleading.\n\n2. `sequence_id` issue: The PRD explicitly says "数据库自
增 bigserial". The code uses Snowflake. The migration has `sequence_id BIGINT NO
T NULL`. The entity has `@Column("bigint")`. This is a clear deviation from the 
PRD and could cause ordering issues if Snowflake IDs are not strictly monotonica
lly increasing within a single database instance. Actually, Snowflake IDs are ti
me-based but not strictly monotonic in insertion order if generated by multiple 
threads/processes. The PRD requires bigserial specifically to guarantee strict o
rdering by insertion. This is a Blocking issue because it violates a core techni
cal requirement.\n\nWait, but maybe `Snowflake.nextId()` in this project is impl
emented to use database sequences? Let me check the Snowflake utility.',
    encrypted=None
)
