    think='I have enough information now to write the review report. Let me summ
arize my findings:\n\n**Blocking Issues:**\n1. **Mandatory checklist items not e
xecuted**: `make test` and `make lint` were skipped. The PR body explicitly stat
es this. According to `docs/exec-plans/templates/TEMPLATE-fullstack-feature.md` 
delivery checklist, these are mandatory. The developer did not complete the full
stack feature template\'s delivery checklist.\n2. **`sequence_id` does not use d
atabase auto-increment `bigserial`**: PRD `prd/v1-im.md` explicitly states "sequ
ence_id 使用数据库自增 bigserial". The implementation uses application-level `Sn
owflake.nextId()` instead. The migration `20250426000000-CreateImTables.ts` crea
tes `sequence_id BIGINT NOT NULL` without `AUTO_INCREMENT`. The entity `MessageE
ntity` uses `@Column("bigint")` without auto-generation. This violates a core te
chnical requirement from the PRD that is critical for message ordering guarantee
.\n\n**Major Issues:**\n3. **Duplicate system messages possible**: `ImService.cr
eateSystemMessage()` (line 198-226 in `im.service.ts`) does not protect against 
duplicate insertion for the same conversation. Since `client_message_id` is `nul
l` for system messages, and MySQL allows multiple `NULL` values in a unique inde
x (`idx_messages_conv_client_msg_id`), re-emitting `match:created` event (e.g., 
retry, race condition) will create duplicate welcome messages. The PRD states: "
打开会话时，若数据库中无系统消息记录，后端自动插入一条".\n4. **PR description in
accuracy regarding `matching.module.ts`**: The PR body claims "更新 matching.mod
ule.ts - 引入 ImModule", but the actual diff for `matching.module.ts` only refac
tors Redis/Jwt module imports and does NOT import `ImModule`. While the event em
itter pattern makes this technically unnecessary, this indicates the developer e
ither did not accurately describe changes or intended an integration that wasn\'
t implemented. More importantly, if there was a direct dependency intended, it\'
s missing.\n\nWait, issue #4 might be too weak for Major. Let me reconsider. The
event emitter approach is actually the better pattern for decoupling. The fact t
hat matching.module.ts doesn\'t import ImModule is correct from an architecture 
perspective. The only issue is the inaccurate PR description. That\'s not really
a code problem. I should probably not list this as Major.\n\nLet me think of ano
ther Major issue.\n\n5. **Missing `make check-contract-sync`**: The template che
cklist includes `make check-contract-sync`. The PR body doesn\'t mention running
it. While generated files exist in both `packages/shared-types/` and `apps/mobil
e/lib/models/generated/im/`, I can\'t verify if they are actually in sync with t
he OpenAPI contract without deeper inspection. But given that the generated file
s exist and look consistent, I\'ll note this as unverified rather than a definit
e issue.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the `im.service.ts` `getConversa
tions` method, there\'s a potential performance issue. It does N+1 Redis calls i
n a loop (line 428-431). But this is acceptable for MVP with small page sizes.\n
\nAnother issue: In `im.gateway.ts`, when `handleSendMessage` succeeds, it emits
`conversation:updated` to both parties. But the `getConversations` API doesn\'t 
return `unread_count` for the sender - only for the requester. So when Alice sen
ds a message, she receives `conversation:updated` but her unread count for that 
conversation shouldn\'t change (it\'s Bob\'s that should). Actually, looking at 
the gateway code, it emits `conversation:updated` with `last_message` only, not 
unread count. So this is fine.\n\nWait, I found another issue in `im.gateway.ts`
:\n- Line 87-96: `message:delivered` is emitted to the sender only if `receiverS
ockets.length > 0`. But `fetchSockets()` only checks if the receiver is currentl
y connected to this specific server instance. In a multi-server deployment with 
Redis adapter, `fetchSockets()` might not work correctly or might require additi
onal configuration. However, for MVP single-server, this is acceptable.\n\nLet m
e look for another real Major issue.\n\nActually, looking at `im_bloc.dart` line
232-280, `_onSendMessage`:\n- It creates a temp message with `id: clientMessageI
d` (which is a UUID v4)\n- It emits `MessageSending` state\n- Then it calls `_so
cketClient!.sendMessage(...)` \n- But the SocketClient sends `client_message_id`
and the server will return a different server-generated `id` in `message:ack`\n-
The BLoC updates the message `id` from `clientMessageId` to `serverMessageId` on
ack\n- This is fine\n\nBut wait, `_onSendMessage` uses `event.clientMessageId ??
const Uuid().v4()`. If `event.clientMessageId` is null, it generates a new UUID.
But when retrying a failed message, the `ChatPage._buildChatItems` sets `onRetry
: () => _sendMessage(msg.content)`. This retry mechanism does NOT pass the origi
nal `clientMessageId`! Let me verify.\n\nIn `chat_page.dart` line 253-255:\n```d
art\nonRetry: msg.status == \'failed\' && msg.senderId == currentUserId\n    ? (
) => _sendMessage(msg.content)\n    : null,\n```\n\nAnd `_sendMessage(String tex
t)` at line 49-59:\n```dart\nvoid _sendMessage(String text) {\n    if (text.trim
().isEmpty) return;\n    final senderId = _currentUserId;\n    if (senderId == n
ull) return;\n    context.read<ImBloc>().add(SendMessage(\n          conversatio
nId: widget.conversationId,\n          content: text.trim(),\n          type: \'
text\',\n          senderId: senderId,\n        ));\n  }\n```\n\nSo when retryin
g, it creates a NEW `SendMessage` event WITHOUT the original `clientMessageId`. 
This means the retry will generate a NEW UUID, and the server won\'t be able to 
deduplicate it if the original message actually did get persisted! This violates
the idempotency requirement.\n\nAccording to PRD v1-im.md: "客户端保留发送队列，
未收到 message:ack 时自动重发" and "客户端生成 client_message_id（UUID v4 或雪花
算法）" and "重复发送时捕获唯一索引冲突，返回已存在的消息记录和 sequence_id". Th
e retry mechanism MUST reuse the original `client_message_id`.\n\nThis is a **Ma
jor** issue because it breaks message idempotency on retry.\n\nLet me verify the
`SendMessage` event class.',
